  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">WATER, SANITATION AND HYGIENE EMERGENCY RESPONSE to IDPs (NEW ARRIVALS) IN GONGULONG, JERE LGA</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">In August 2017, Boko Haram attacked Ngudda, Buta villages of Mafa LGA, and Kesakura village of Jere LGA which has resulted in loss of lives and displacement of an estimated population of 8700 people who eventually settled in the not distant Gongulong community. The influx of people on top of the existing number if IDPs has resulted in the lack of clean drinking water, open defecation and poor hygiene practices thus, urgent action is needed to prevent disease outbreaks. This project will address these needs (clean water and open defecation) by providing access to clean drinking water (2 motorized borehole and 6 hand pumps), sanitation facilities (60 units of VIP latrines), hygiene and dignity kits (1450 hygiene kits) distribution and hygiene promotion campaigns (door to door visit, FGD and IEC) to 8700 newly arrived displaced persons in Gongulong Lawanti and Gongulong Bulamari villages. The target population for this project are the newly arrived IDPs with no or limited access to safe drinking water, improved sanitation facilities and good hygiene practices the host communities will be indirectly benefiting from the projects as well.</narrative>
  </description>
